# dbt validation commands

Single source of truth for validation commands. Specialist agents reference this file instead of duplicating command blocks.

## Baseline (every change)

```bash
dbt parse
dbt compile --select <model>+
```

## Standard model change

```bash
dbt build --select <model>+
```

Equivalent split when debugging:

```bash
dbt run --select <model>+
dbt test --select <model>+
```

## Incremental models

After config or logic changes:

```bash
dbt run --select <model>          # normal incremental first
dbt run --select <model> --full-refresh   # required when columns added/removed or logic needs backfill
dbt test --select <model>+
```

State `--full-refresh` requirement in the PR when schema or incremental logic changes.

## PR / multi-model validation

When reviewing a branch diff (requires prior `dbt compile` or `dbt run` to populate manifest):

```bash
dbt parse
dbt build --select state:modified+
```

When state selection is unavailable, name changed models explicitly:

```bash
dbt parse
dbt build --select <changed_models>+
```

## Source freshness

```bash
dbt source freshness --select source:<name>
```

## Metric or schema work (add to build)

- Before/after row counts on affected models
- Core metric totals comparison
- Looker Studio field check (exposure YAML)
- Civis job selectors if model names or tags changed

